observations.conclusion:
I was ready to go identified because ultimately I do believe it's a match but due to poor quality and clarity (ridges are very dotty and broken) and perhaps relying on the form too much I decided against. Feeling indecisive today, I think on another day I might have identified!

Level 3  features were creases.

Degree of similarity - 4 

Degree of support - 3

(C) Degree of Similarity = 4
(E) Degree of Support = 5

Degree of similarity - High
Degree of Support - 4

I am surprised by how many features I have found in comparison at this stage, as my initial thoughts were that the mark was fairly poor quality at the analysis stage due to the low confidence in the location of many of the features. However during the comparison stage I found no differences that weren't explainable. The swipe mark and general background interference is distorting some features, but overall I am very confident in this identification. 
I found a lot of extra features at the comparison stage which I dint see in the analysis stage, I think I left a lot out initially due to the low clarity of a lot if the features.

Degree of similarity: 3

Degree of support: 4

Degree of similarity - 4
Degree of support - 3

Due to low quality of mark, I feel I am being influenced by features in the print. While there are a number of features in agreement and I can't see any in disagreement, I still wouldn't make an identification on such a poor mark.

High degree of similarity but there are a number of features within the known impression that I cannot locate in the unknown. This could be down to poor clarity but cannot make assumptions.
The core also appears different, probably as a result of poor clarity, dotted ridges and light deposition pressure. There are a couple of features in agreement that were located by relying on the known impression so I would not class those as high confidence features eg pairing no. 14, 15

Support for inconclusive

Degree of Similarity - 4 High Level of similarity. some difference in terms of placement of feature but explainable by the slippage and twisting. 
Degree of Support - 4 Supported identification.
